{"id":"10898","name":"Wordle import/export","tagline":"Migrate your Wordle game from one iOS device to another","icon":"ios14 c4292093695 g59405","latest":"31814","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>This shortcut allows to import and export the state of the Wordle game via iOS’ Universal Clipboard, allowing to change the device the game is played from without losing the stats.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>⚠️ <strong>WARNING: Incompatible data</strong> ⚠️</p>\n<p>Importing data from <em>powerlanguage.co.uk</em> into <em>www.nytimes.com</em> doesn't work. Use the <a href=\"https://twitter.com/NYTimesWordplay/status/1492169525244092417\">official migration path</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://atnbueno.com/wordle-20220122.png\"></p>\n<p>The game uses JavaScript's <em>localStorage</em> to save the current game and the stats. This shortcuts saves/restores that data in iOS' Universal Clipboard, which synchronizes between devices under the same Apple ID, obfuscating it with Base64 to avoid accidentally spoiling oneself with the day's solution.</p>\n<p>Since version 1.1.0 both the <a href=\"https://www.powerlanguage.co.uk/wordle/\">original game</a> and the <a href=\"https://wordle.danielfrg.com/\">Spanish version</a> are supported.</p>\n<p>Version 1.2.0 switched the original game to <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/games/wordle/index.html\">its new home at NYT</a>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatible with iOS 14/15</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://gist.github.com/atnbueno/f8bc6376bcdb1d8dace2c490f9ac0770\"><em>Greasemonkey</em> script for Firefox</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/API/Window/localStorage\"><code>Window.localStorage</code> documentation at MDN</a></li>\n</ul>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.2.0 - Feb. 13, 2022, 9:58 a.m.</strong></p><p>Switched original game to nytimes.com<br>(WARNING: incompatible data. Read the description.)</p>"}